type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Olney I was born in 1220, in Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died in 1265, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1220–1265":"1220–1265","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","onley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1220–1265":"1220–1265","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","onley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1220–1265":"1220–1265","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","onley, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","haversham, Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Olney I est né en 1220, à Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1265, à Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 45 ans."},"de":{"1220–1265":"1220–1265","12